reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Great jeans. Ordered true to size and they fit just as they should. Will end up buying more pairs of these jeans in the future.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 18, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars STOP SCROLLING! Best fitting jeans here!
reviews.reviewText: 502 have to be the most comfortable cut of all the Levi's I have ever tried. Especially these. They are a stretch material even though they don't look like it. They are made to be at hip level, where most people wear jeans, not waist level. Well done Levi's!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2024
reviews.reviewText: They always fit me well, last long & reasonably priced.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Seller shipped WRONG sized pants
reviews.reviewText: The pants wasn’t tapered at all and it was an inch too long. I went back to the same pants and read all the reviews confirming lack of quality and control from the seller.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I love these jeans! I have two pairs and they are a true fit. Im a lil chunky 5’7 200lbs so I got a 33x32 they are a lil tight but I like em snugg…

reviews.reviewText: I bought these on a sale and ended up loving them. They have a little bit of fashion color to them and they look very fashionable. They are very comfortable.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 27, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Blew out crotch after maybe 50 wears
reviews.reviewText: Crotch blew after 50 or so wears. Fabric wore itself thin and split. I had some older 521s that probably got 200 wears before that happened. These weren't everyday for me, but comfortable. They're soft for a denim, but Not durable.
